<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 7:15PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of west central Pondera
and south central Glacier Counties through 800 PM MDT...
At 714 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms near
East Glacier Park, moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Kiowa, East Glacier Park Village, East Glacier Park, Heart Butte,
South Browning and Starr School.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Persons in campgrounds should consider seeking sturdy shelter until
this storm passes.</instruction>
